opt760.d1:
{Collector}
{+@Effect@%} chance to pick up an extra resource.
Every rank gives a guaranteed extra resource.

opt760.d9:
{Courier}
{+@Effect@} to the maximum number of
the hero's movement points.

opt760.d14:
{Scholar}
The hero now has a {@Effect@%} chance to further increase a
 random stat when leveling up on the map.

opt760.c0:
{Treasure-hunter}
Rank is given for every 3 
open treasure chests.

opt760.c1:
{Collector}
Rank is given for every 5
resource piles picked up.

opt760.c2:
{Dragonbane}
Rank is given for every conquered 
Dragon Utopia.

opt760.c3:
{Raider}
Rank is given for every third
creature bank looted.

opt760.c4:
{Wisdom Seeker}
Rank is given for every 3 spells
learned from magic shrines.

opt760.c5:
{Inspector}
Rank is given for every single captured
mine (unflagged/idle).

opt760.c9:
{Courier}
Rank is given for every
completed seer task.

opt760.c10:
{Witcher}
Rank is given for each training
done for a skill in a witch hut.

opt760.c11:
{Defender}
Rank is given for each
siege defended in your city.

opt760.c12:
{Invader}
Rank is given for every
two cities taken with a battle.

opt760.c13:
{Slayer}
Rank is given for every
two enemy heroes defeated.

opt760.c14:
{Scholar}
Rank is given for every 3 objects
visited on the map that increases a stat.

opt760.t0:
After opening a treasure chest,
@HeroName@ gets the new achievement:

{Treasure-hunter [Rank @Rang@]}

The gold/exp found in chests is increased by {@Effect@}.

opt760.t1:
After collecting resources,
@HeroName@ gets the new achievement:

{Collector [Rank @Rang@]}

Increased chance to pick up more resources.

opt760.t2:
After conquering a Dragon Utopia,
@HeroName@ gets the new achievement:

{Dragonbane [Rank @Rang@]}

Weakens enemy dragons (living) reducing their speed and defense by {@Effect@}.

opt760.t3:
After capturing a creature bank,
@HeroName@ gets the new achievement:

{Raider [Rank @Rang@]}

The hero's unit's speed increases by {@Effect@} when raiding a creature bank.

opt760.t4:
After learning a spell in a shrine,
@HeroName@ gets the new achievement:

{Wisdom Seeker [Rank @Rang@]}

Knowledge is increased by {@Effect@}.

opt760.t5:
After starting production and performing an inspection,
@HeroName@ gets the new achievement:

{Inspector [Rank @Rang@]}

When capturing an idle mine the hero recieves additional resources for {@Effect@} day(s) of work.

opt760.t6:
After defeating "good" units on the map,
@HeroName@ gets the new achievement:

{Punisher [Rank @Rang@]}

Units on the map belonging to "good" factions recieve {+@Effect@} to attack and {-@Effect@} to defense (minimum defense = 0) when in battle against the hero.

opt760.t7:
After defeating "evil" units on the map,
@HeroName@ gets the new achievement:

{Inquisitor [Rank @Rang@]}

Units on the map belonging to "evil" factions recieve {+@Effect@} to attack and {-@Effect@} to defense (minimum defense = 0) when in battle against the hero.

opt760.t8:
After defeating "neutral" units on the map,
@HeroName@ gets the new achievement:

{Ruffian [Rank @Rang@]}

Units on the map belonging to "neutral" factions recieve {+@Effect@} to attack and {-@Effect@} to defense (minimum defense = 0) when in battle against the hero.

opt760.t9:
After completing a quest for a seer,
@HeroName@ gets the new achievement:

{Courier  [Rank @Rang@]}

The hero gets {+@Effect@} to his/her maximum movement points.

opt760.t10:
After learning a new skill from a witch,
@HeroName@ gets the new achievement:

{Witcher [Rank @Rang@]}

At the beginning of a round there is a {@Effect@%} chance to inflict damage to a random enemy unit for 3 turns.

opt760.t11:
After successfully defending against a siege,
@HeroName@ gets the new achievement:

{Defender [Rank @Rang@]}

Arrow towers have a {@Effect@%} chance to poison an enemy unit.

opt760.t12:
After successfully capturing a city,
@HeroName@ gets the new achievement:

{Invader [Rank @Rang@]}

The hero's catapult has a {@Effect@%} chance to launch a 2nd shot.

opt760.t13:
After defeating a hero,
@HeroName@ gets the new achievement:

{Slayer [Rank @Rang@]}

Enemy units have a {@Effect@%} chance to freeze in terror before their turn begins.

opt760.t14:
After visiting an object and increasing primary skill points,
@HeroName@ gets the new achievement:

{Scholar [Rank @Rang@]}

The hero has a {@Effect@%} chance of getting an additional primary skill point when visiting an object on the map that increases them.
